pec

Interface IPec<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - is the generic type for the elements in the PEC.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PriorityQueuePec

    public interface IPec<T>
    Interface relative to the PEC. If there is a need to use a PEC with a different implementation (for example using a HashSet or something similar) one can do so by implementing this interface
    Author:
    group2

    • Method Detail

      • getNumElements

        int getNumElements()
        Getter method for the number of elements in the PEC. Since the PEC is in another package we need the getter so the variables can remain package.
        Returns:
        is the number of elements in the PEC.

      • addElement

        boolean addElement(T element,
                   java.util.Comparator<T> c)
        Method to add a new element to the PEC. There is also the need to provide a comparator that makes explicit the way we want to sort the elements.
        Parameters:
        element - is the element we wish to add to the PEC.
        c - is the comparator that we wish to use to sort our PEC.
        Returns:
        is true in case of success and false otherwise

      • getFirstElement

        T getFirstElement()
        Getter method for the first element of the PEC. This method not only returns the first element but also removes it from the PEC.
        Returns:
        is the first element in the PEC that invokes the method.

      • getElementList

        java.util.Collection<T> getElementList()
        Getter method for the whole element list. This allows us to iterate over it, for example.
        Returns:
        is the element list inside the PEC.
